---
import '../styles/why.css';
---
<section class="why" id="why">
  <div class="why-inner">
    <p class="why-eyebrow">An editorial on why this work matters.</p>
    <h2 class="why-lead">
      A budget&rsquo;s ripple effect, a policy&rsquo;s second-order consequence, a program&rsquo;s real return &mdash;
      <em>these aren&rsquo;t footnotes.</em>
      They are the case for the work itself.
    </h2>
    <div class="why-body">
      <p class="why-graf">
        Economic impact and policy analysis measures how an organization&rsquo;s spending, hiring, and operations ripple through a regional economy &mdash; and how policy decisions shape who benefits. It turns budgets, programs, and policy alternatives into a clear map of consequences.
      </p>
      <p class="why-graf why-graf--diff">
        Traditional tools rely on modeled estimates and outdated national averages updated every few years. Lumecon applies rigorous methods to administrative and high-frequency data, so the results reflect <em>your</em> economy &mdash; not a generic assumption.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
